        "subject": "LU-723 External lustre-ldiskfs package integration",
        "message": "LU-723 External lustre-ldiskfs package integration\n\nAdd a configure option --with-ldiskfs-devel to build Lustre against an\nexternally maintained ldiskfs package. This package maintains ldiskfs\nas a standalone code base. The intention is to make the ldiskfs API\nand dependencies explicit and to have a clear layering between ldiskfs\nand Lustre. With the addition of alternate OSDs building ldiskfs\nshould become optional.\n\nSigned-off-by: Ned Bass <bass6@llnl.gov>\nSigned-off-by: Prakash Surya <surya1@llnl.gov>\nSigned-off-by: Brian Behlendorf <behlendorf1@llnl.gov>\nChange-Id: Iaa17d0483e155439c8de206af81f19a321bbeaa1\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
